He is rude when you ask him questions and is not helpful. He does not cover theoretical parts of the course and will only copy examples that are posted online in class. Would definitely not recommend taking any of his classes.
Go to school and listen the lecture, easily got A. The midterm and Final questions all from the class lecture.

Go to class take his notes and do the practice questions and assignments because they are the same questions in the test. He wants students to do good. Overall the best so far.

Good Prof. Does not post lectures online and are all handwritten so be prepared to attend every lecture or have someone you know in class. Exams are relatively straight forward since they are taken directly from the assignments and the question sets that he posts. Probably one of the best prof's to take any economics course with.

Tests are not easy, however the tests strongly reflected the assignments. If you did the assignments the test questions should all look familiar. Furthermore, he gave two midterms and only counted the better mark. Strong accent makes him a bit difficult to understand and notes are intensive (but worth taking). I would strongly recommend.

Really helpful prof. If you attended all the lectures then you would know what would be expected. The textbook isn't really necessary except for the occasional practice question. Final exam was harder than midterms, but overall a really great prof for a class that is all theory. Am looking forward to taking another class with him in the future!

Midterms were decent and came straight from the class notes and examples posted online. Exam was harder. He's very unclear in his lectures, very unhelpful in his office hours and very unprofessional when emailing. Not hard to do well, but only if the textbook becomes your best friend
Frustrating teacher. Knows his stuff but is unclear about his expectations toward students. Also surprisingly rude. Not recommended.
